-- Romania’s Alro Invested $15 Million to Cut Energy Consumption
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-06-28T06:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-28/romania-s-alro-invested-15-million-to-cut-energy-consumption.html
Alro SA (ALR) , a Romanian aluminum
producer, said it invested $15 million in the first five months
to increase its  energy efficiency .  This year’s investment adds to the $77 million already
spent by the company since 2005 to reduce its energy
consumption, it said in a filing to the Bucharest Stock Exchange
today. The Slatina, Romania-based company is majority owned by
Vimetco NV.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
